          "date": "2025-06-13 01:30:56.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-06-16 01:54:16.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-0000 flr: add mirror error LVB creation",
        "message": "LU-0000 flr: add mirror error LVB creation\n\nTODO: The demo code is still present, which is sort of good because\nwe're only going to put the errors in if we're using DIO, not AIO\nor buffered IO.\n\nAIO is going to stink here.\n\nNext item - if you're going to pursue this - is having the server\ndo something intelligent with this info, ie, parse it and use it\nwhen handling errors.  That means you'll need that new flag too.\n----\n\nAdd infrastructure to create mirror error LVB data for Active Writer\nlock cancellation:\n\n- Add ldlm_mirror_error_lvb structure with magic, mirror_count, and\n  flexible array of mirror error codes\n- Add ldlm_create_mirror_error_lvb() helper function to create LVB\n  data from mirror error arrays\n- Integrate LVB creation in ll_file_io_generic() after DIO completion\n  for immediate mirror files\n- LVB contains simple integer array with one error code per mirror\n\nThe LVB data will be sent to the server during Active Writer lock\ncancellation to communicate per-mirror I/O results.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ia9067534b405e4f6e15b57a4102fed8c0563842c\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
